SIMPLE: tuber
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuber
<hw>Tu"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[L., a hump. knob;
probably akin to <ets>tumere</ets> to swell. Cf. <er>Tumid</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A fleshy, rounded stem
or root, usually containing starchy matter, as the potato or arrowroot;
a thickened root-stock. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Tuberous</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A genus of fungi. See
<er>Truffle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A tuberosity; a
tubercle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tube railway</ent>⟦br⟧
